If I close the linear editor using escape things work normally, but if I close it by clicking on the canvas this happens:
(Clicking on the buttons does nothing)

https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/a17d23c3-dd6d-4fdb-913f-d14e325fb584

This is because in `onPointerUpFromPointerDownHandler` the `selectionElement` is set to `null` but this is overwritten when `actionFinalize` is called.

## 2.
Another problem is that in `actionFinalize` the `selectedLinearElement` is set to `null` but `selectedElementIds` remain as is. This is inconsistent, if you want to move points of the linear element around after closing the linear editor, you need to unselect and reselect it:

https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/b1864fd2-06ab-4f3b-80c0-05ccd1856c61

## 3. 
Linear editor is not always opened using actionToggleLinearEditor

Additionally the `actionToggleLinearEditor` is not being used to toggle the linear editor when being opened with `(ENTER,CTRL_OR_CMD)` or `CTRL_OR_CMD` and double click. The `actionToggleLinearElement`'s predicate function is also implemented (slightly differently) in both of these places:

1. 
```
if (isLinearElement(selectedElement)) {
  if (
    !this.state.editingLinearElement ||
    this.state.editingLinearElement.elementId !==
      selectedElements[0].id
  ) {
    this.store.shouldCaptureIncrement();
    if (!isElbowArrow(selectedElement)) {
      this.setState({
        editingLinearElement: new LinearElementEditor(
          selectedElement,
        ),
      });
    }
  }
}
 ```
 2. 
 ```
if (selectedElements.length === 1 && isLinearElement(selectedElements[0])) {
    if (
      event[KEYS.CTRL_OR_CMD] &&
      (!this.state.editingLinearElement ||
        this.state.editingLinearElement.elementId !==
          selectedElements[0].id) &&
      !isElbowArrow(selectedElements[0])
    ) {
      this.store.shouldCaptureIncrement();
      this.setState({
        editingLinearElement: new LinearElementEditor(selectedElements[0]),
      });
      return;
    }
 ```
 
 Both of these could simply be replaced by:
```
 this.actionManager.isActionEnabled(actionToggleLinearEditor) &&
  this.actionManager.executeAction(actionToggleLinearEditor, "keyboard");
```

